<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-11-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-11-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="575" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d575">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Loomis</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Barrett</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-11-17"><hi rend="italic">November 17,
                                    1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Loomis informs Mr. Barrett that the Secretary of War will be the
                            guests of the Panama Canal Commission and of this Government, and that
                            the fleet will remain at Panama. Instructs him to inform the President
                            of Panama.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>